<TITLE> Man dies in police custody in capital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 9 (bdnews24.com)  A 45-year old man, arrested eight days ago on a car theft charge, died Tuesday after being remanded into police custody. According to the police, Zakir Hossain fell ill at Ramna Police Station and was taken to Dhaka Medical College Hospital where duty doctors declared him dead at about 2pm. Magistrates had ordered Zakir to be taken into police custody for questioning just 24 hours before on Monday. Ramna police chief Shibli Noman refused to comment on the circumstances of his death until a post-mortem was done. Human rights organisations in Bangladesh regularly raise concerns about police torture of accused in custody. 
